    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix version mismatch handling in telnetsrv shared library loader\n\n### Summary\nThe `telnetsrv_checkbuildver` function was not properly reporting version mismatches between the main executable and shared libraries. The function always returned 0, even when versions didn't match, causing the loader to continue loading incompatible modules instead of aborting.\n\nThis fix ensures version mismatches are properly detected and reported to the loader.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv.c`: Modified `telnetsrv_checkbuildver` to return -1 on version mismatch\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv.h`: Added function declaration and checkverfunc_t typedef\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Compile the code with mismatched versions between main executable and telnetsrv shared library\n2. Observe that the loader continues to load the module despite version mismatch\n3. With fix applied, the loader will abort when version mismatch is detected\n\nThe symptom is that incompatible modules are loaded which can lead to undefined behavior or crashes at runtime.\n"
}